[div class=p 
	"As mentioned 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=here|href=/Forum/Posts/536584)
	", completing only one loop (one complete building) of the game is sufficient for publication.  A run that chose to continue until a later completion point (i.e. end of difficulty increase/new content) would obsolete this run despite being a longer run itself.  As I mentioned in my opinion in the thread, 6 buildings (loops) would exhaust new content from what I can deduce from 
	[a href=https://archive.org/details/beauty-and-the-beast-intellivision/page/n3/mode/2up rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"the game's manual
	]a
	"; while speculated that end of difficulty increase is aroudn the 5th building, it is not currently clear where difficulty stops increasing.
	$LF
